# Project Overview and Technology Stack

## Context
- This rule provides foundational information about the FastApi Template
- Should be considered for all code generation and modifications
- Essential for understanding the project's architecture and dependencies

## Requirements
- Use FastAPI as the web framework
- Python version must be 3.13 or higher
- Use PostgreSQL with asyncpg driver for database operations
- SQLAlchemy 2.0+ with async support for ORM
- UV as the package manager (NOT pip or poetry)
- Uvicorn for local development, Gunicorn for dev/prod environments
- Follow the established directory structure without deviation

## Directory Structure
```
app/
├── api/               # API routes and endpoints
│   ├── health/       # Health check endpoints
│   └── v1/           # API version 1
├── config/           # Configuration and settings
├── exceptions/       # Custom exception classes
├── middlewares/      # FastAPI middlewares
├── models/           # SQLAlchemy ORM models
├── repositories/     # Data access layer
├── schema/           # Pydantic schemas and API response models
├── services/         # Business logic layer
└── utils/            # Utility functions and constants

libs/
├── database/         # Database configuration and migrations
│   └── migrations/   # Alembic migrations
└── logger/           # Custom logging configuration

tests/
├── factories/        # Test factories using factory-boy
└── helpers/          # Test utilities
```

